rlDot3adAgg.name: rlDot3adAgg
rlDot3adAgg.description: The private MIB module definition for trunk support in Dell-VRTX devices.

rlDot3adAggMibVersion.name: rlDot3adAggMibVersion
rlDot3adAggMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 1.

rlDot3adAggBalanceTable.name: rlDot3adAggBalanceTable
rlDot3adAggBalanceTable.description: An entry of this table specifies a balancing criterion used for the corresponding dot3adAggIndex.

rlDot3adAggBalanceEntry.name: rlDot3adAggBalanceEntry
rlDot3adAggBalanceEntry.description: A list of information for each dot3adAggIndex.

rlDot3adAggBalanceForwardType.name: rlDot3adAggBalanceForwardType
rlDot3adAggBalanceForwardType.description: A Forwarding type: Bridging or Routing.

rlDot3adAggBalanceLayer.name: rlDot3adAggBalanceLayer
rlDot3adAggBalanceLayer.description: A Network Layer Number, may have the following values: 2, 3 or 4. The default value is: Bridging: 2 Routing: 3.

rlDot3adAggBalanceUsedAddresses.name: rlDot3adAggBalanceUsedAddresses
rlDot3adAggBalanceUsedAddresses.description: Specifies the Network Layer addresses used for Balancing of unicast frames. The function sets the criterion (by layer and used address in it).

rlDot3adAggBalanceBroadcastType.name: rlDot3adAggBalanceBroadcastType
rlDot3adAggBalanceBroadcastType.description: Specifies a balancing criterion used for L2 broadcast and unknown frames: common: a link allocated for broadcast and unknown frames is used for unicast frames too dedicated: a link allocated for broadcast and unknown frames is not used for unicast frames

rlDot3adAggNumOfTrunks.name: rlDot3adAggNumOfTrunks
rlDot3adAggNumOfTrunks.description: The number of trunks supported by the device.

rlDot3adAggMaxPortsInTrunks.name: rlDot3adAggMaxPortsInTrunks
rlDot3adAggMaxPortsInTrunks.description: The maximun number of ports in a trunk.

rlDot3adAggTrunkCreationSupport.name: rlDot3adAggTrunkCreationSupport
rlDot3adAggTrunkCreationSupport.description: Specifies if there is support to rldot3adAggCreationTable, and the type of the support: supportedTrunkOrLacp - ports that are members in some trunk are belongs to it by manual configuration or by lacp, but not togther. notSupported - there is not support to rldot3adAggCreationTable.

rlDot3adAggCreationTable.name: rlDot3adAggCreationTable
rlDot3adAggCreationTable.description: An entry of this table is for creation of an aggregator for the corresponding dot3adAggIndex, when the value of the rlDot3adAggCreationSupport is diffrent from notSupported.

rlDot3adAggCreationTrunk.name: rlDot3adAggCreationTrunk
rlDot3adAggCreationTrunk.description: The aggregator can aggregate ports in manual configuration.

rlDot3adAggCreationLacp.name: rlDot3adAggCreationLacp
rlDot3adAggCreationLacp.description: The aggregator can aggregate ports by lacp.

rlDot3adAggLoadBalancingPerTrunk.name: rlDot3adAggLoadBalancingPerTrunk
rlDot3adAggLoadBalancingPerTrunk.description: Specifies if load balancing is defined per trunk or per device.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpTable.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpTable
rlDot3adAggPortLacpTable.description: An entry of this table specifies lacp protocol state and statistics for the corresponding dot3adAggPortIndex.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpEntry.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpEntry
rlDot3adAggPortLacpEntry.description: A list of information for each dot3adAggPortIndex.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpPdusRx.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpPdusRx
rlDot3adAggPortLacpPdusRx.description: The number of valid LACPDUs received on this Aggregation Port. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpPDUsTx.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpPDUsTx
rlDot3adAggPortLacpPDUsTx.description: The number of LACPDUs transmitted on this Aggregation Port. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpRxState.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpRxState
rlDot3adAggPortLacpRxState.description: This attribute holds the value 'current' if the Receive state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the CURRENT state, 'expired' if the Receive state machine is in the EXPIRED state, 'defaulted' if the Receive state machine is in the DEFAULTED state, 'initialize' if the Receive state machine is in the INITIALIZE state, 'portDisabled' if the Receive state machine is in the PORT_DISABLED state, or 'lacpDisabled' if the Receive state machine is in the LACP_DISABLED state. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpMuxState.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpMuxState
rlDot3adAggPortLacpMuxState.description: This attribute holds the value 'detached' if the Mux state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the DETACHED state, 'waiting' if the Mux state machine is in the WAITING state, 'attached' if the Mux state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the ATTACHED state, 'collecting' if the Mux state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the COLLECTING state, 'distributing' if the Mux state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the DISTRIBUTING state, and 'collecting_ distributing' if the Mux state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the COLLECTING_DISTRIBUTING state. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpPeriodicState.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpPeriodicState
rlDot3adAggPortLacpPeriodicState.description: This attribute holds the value 'noPeriodic' if the Periodic state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the NO_PERIODIC state, 'fastPeriodic' if the Mux state machine is in the FAST_PERIODIC state, 'slowPeriodic' if the Mux state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the SLOW_PERIODIC state, or 'periodicTx' if the Periodic state machine for the Aggregation Port is in the PERIODIC_TX state. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpSelected.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpSelected
rlDot3adAggPortLacpSelected.description: This attribute holds the value 'unselected' if the Selected variable for the Aggregation Port is set to UNSELECTED, 'selected' if the Selected variable for the Aggregation Port is set to SELECTED, or 'waiting' if the Selected variable for the Aggregation Port is set to WAITING. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpReady.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpReady
rlDot3adAggPortLacpReady.description: A read-only Boolean value indicating whether the Aggregation Port is in the WAITING state in the Mux state machine and its wait_while_timer has expired ('TRUE'). otherwise, its valus is 'FALSE'.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpPortMoved.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpPortMoved
rlDot3adAggPortLacpPortMoved.description: A read-only Boolean value indicating whether the Partner_Oper_System or Partner_Oper_Port_Number in use by the Aggregation Port has been changed in an incoming LACPDU ('TRUE'). otherwise, its valus is 'FALSE'.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpNNT.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpNNT
rlDot3adAggPortLacpNNT.description: A read-only Boolean value indicating whether there is a new protocol information that should be transmitted on the link, or that the Partner needs to be reminded of the old information. otherwise, its valus is 'FALSE'.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpPeriodicTxTimer.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpPeriodicTxTimer
rlDot3adAggPortLacpPeriodicTxTimer.description: The amount of time in seconds remaining before the Periodeic Tx timer will expire. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpCurrentWhileTimer.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpCurrentWhileTimer
rlDot3adAggPortLacpCurrentWhileTimer.description: The amount of time in seconds remaining before the Current While timer will expire. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggPortLacpWaitWhileTimer.name: rlDot3adAggPortLacpWaitWhileTimer
rlDot3adAggPortLacpWaitWhileTimer.description: The amount of time in seconds remaining before the Wait While timer will expire. This value is read-only.

rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsSup.name: rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsSupport
rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsSup.description: Specifies if there is support to rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsTable.

rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsTab.name: rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsTable
rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsTab.description: An entry of this table specifies membership restrictions for ports that lacp is enbaled on them, and try to attach to the corresponding dot3adAggIndex.

rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsEnt.name: rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsEntry
rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsEnt.description: A list of information for each dot3adAggIndex.

rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPar.name: rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPartnerAdminKey
rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPar.description: This variable specifies the administrative key of the remote LACP aggregator. A value of 0 is returned if the value of the variable hasn't been set.

rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsSpe.name: rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsSpeedAdminMode
rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsSpe.description: This variable specifies the required speed of the LACP aggregator in bits per second. A value of 10 is returned for 10G. A value of 0 is returned if the value of the variable hasn't been set.

rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPar.name: rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPartnerAdminSystemId
rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPar.description: This variable specifies the administrative MAC Address of the remote LACP aggregator. A null mac address is returned if the value of the variable hasn't been set.

rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPar.name: rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPartnerAdminSystemPriority
rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsPar.description: This variable specifies the administrative System Priority of the remote LACP aggregator. A value of 0 is returned if the value of the variable hasn't been set.

rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsInd.name: rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsIndividualAggregator
rlDot3adAggLacpMembershipRestrictionsInd.description: This variable specifies if the lacp aggregator represents an Aggregate ('FALSE') or an Individual link ('TRUE').
